cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on understanding the behavior of crowd workers over long periods of time, specifically in the context of microtask crowdsourcing. This suggests a strong emphasis on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY), as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper utilizes natural language processing techniques to analyze the large datasets, indicating a potential connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
